# Bootstrap a new React project with npx and create-react-app

## About 
- Instructor: Andy Van Slaars (@avanslaars)
- Watch video: https://egghead.io/lessons/react-bootstrap-a-new-react-project-with-npx-and-create-react-app
- GitHub Repo: https://github.com/avanslaars/egghead-studydeck/tree/01_npx_cra

## Instructions
1. Create create app using npx command
```
npx create-react-app study_deck
```
- npx:
- create-react-app
- study_deck

2. CHECK IT
```
npx start
```
- Important to know (and see) if it got installed correctly before moving foward so open up your repo in your editor to view the files, package.json, etc
- Instead of `npx start` it can also be `yarn start` but it just needs be the language that you had installed before
- If you're like uhhh what then go here


### Quick Clean Up
This is optional but for the sake of the code along do the following.

- In `App.css` <br/>
<input type="checkbox">  Delete all the code in `App.css` <br/>

- In `App.js` <br/>
<input type="checkbox">  Delete everything between the divs<br/>
<input type="checkbox">  Add `hello world` in between the divs <br/>
<input type="checkbox">  Remove className<br/>


- In `App.test.js` <br/>
<input type="checkbox">  Delete entire file<br/>



